15/*! \file dns/dlz_dlopen.h */
16
17#ifndef DLZ_DLOPEN_H
18#define DLZ_DLOPEN_H
19
20#include <inttypes.h>
21#include <stdbool.h>
22
23#include <dns/sdlz.h>
24
25ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
26
27/*
28 * This header provides a minimal set of defines and typedefs needed
29 * for the entry points of an external DLZ module for bind9.
30 */
31
32#define DLZ_DLOPEN_VERSION 3
33#define DLZ_DLOPEN_AGE 0
34
35/*
36 * dlz_dlopen_version() is required for all DLZ external drivers. It
37 * should return DLZ_DLOPEN_VERSION
38 */
39typedef int dlz_dlopen_version_t(unsigned int *flags);
40
41/*
42 * dlz_dlopen_create() is required for all DLZ external drivers.
43 */
44typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_create_t(const char *dlzname,
45 unsigned int argc,
46 char *argv[],
47 void **dbdata,
48 ...);
49
50/*
51 * dlz_dlopen_destroy() is optional, and will be called when the
52 * driver is unloaded if supplied
53 */
54typedef void dlz_dlopen_destroy_t(void *dbdata);
55
56/*
57 * dlz_dlopen_findzonedb() is required for all DLZ external drivers
58 */
59typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_findzonedb_t(void *dbdata,
60 const char *name,
61 dns_clientinfomethods_t *methods,
62 dns_clientinfo_t *clientinfo);
63
64/*
65 * dlz_dlopen_lookup() is required for all DLZ external drivers
66 */
67typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_lookup_t(const char *zone,
68 const char *name,
69 void *dbdata,
70 dns_sdlzlookup_t *lookup,
71 dns_clientinfomethods_t *methods,
72 dns_clientinfo_t *clientinfo);
73
74/*
75 * dlz_dlopen_authority is optional() if dlz_dlopen_lookup()
76 * supplies authority information for the dns record
77 */
78typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_authority_t(const char *zone,
79 void *dbdata,
80 dns_sdlzlookup_t *lookup);
81
82/*
83 * dlz_dlopen_allowzonexfr() is optional, and should be supplied if
84 * you want to support zone transfers
85 */
86typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_allowzonexfr_t(void *dbdata,
87 const char *name,
88 const char *client);
89
90/*
91 * dlz_dlopen_allnodes() is optional, but must be supplied if supply a
92 * dlz_dlopen_allowzonexfr() function
93 */
94typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_allnodes_t(const char *zone,
95 void *dbdata,
96 dns_sdlzallnodes_t *allnodes);
97
98/*
99 * dlz_dlopen_newversion() is optional. It should be supplied if you
100 * want to support dynamic updates.
101 */
102typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_newversion_t(const char *zone,
103 void *dbdata,
104 void **versionp);
105
106/*
107 * dlz_closeversion() is optional, but must be supplied if you supply
108 * a dlz_newversion() function
109 */
110typedef void dlz_dlopen_closeversion_t(const char *zone,
111 bool commit,
112 void *dbdata,
113 void **versionp);
114
115/*
116 * dlz_dlopen_configure() is optional, but must be supplied if you
117 * want to support dynamic updates
118 */
119typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_configure_t(dns_view_t *view,
120 dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdb,
121 void *dbdata);
122
123/*
124 * dlz_dlopen_setclientcallback() is optional, but must be supplied if you
125 * want to retrieve information about the client (e.g., source address)
126 * before sending a replay.
127 */
128typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_setclientcallback_t(dns_view_t *view,
129 void *dbdata);
130
131
132/*
133 * dlz_dlopen_ssumatch() is optional, but must be supplied if you want
134 * to support dynamic updates
135 */
136typedef bool dlz_dlopen_ssumatch_t(const char *signer,
137 const char *name,
138 const char *tcpaddr,
139 const char *type,
140 const char *key,
141 uint32_t keydatalen,
142 unsigned char *keydata,
143 void *dbdata);
144
145/*
146 * dlz_dlopen_addrdataset() is optional, but must be supplied if you
147 * want to support dynamic updates
148 */
149typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_addrdataset_t(const char *name,
150 const char *rdatastr,
151 void *dbdata,
152 void *version);
153
154/*
155 * dlz_dlopen_subrdataset() is optional, but must be supplied if you
156 * want to support dynamic updates
157 */
158typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_subrdataset_t(const char *name,
159 const char *rdatastr,
160 void *dbdata,
161 void *version);
162
163/*
164 * dlz_dlopen_delrdataset() is optional, but must be supplied if you
165 * want to support dynamic updates
166 */
167typedef isc_result_t dlz_dlopen_delrdataset_t(const char *name,
168 const char *type,
169 void *dbdata,
170 void *version);
171
172ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
173
174#endif
175
